/*
 * Smart_Probe_H2_v2.cpp
 * Created: April 2026
 *
 * Ported from T5 Sensor Simulator V2.7 (Python) to ATtiny3224.
 * V2 fixes vs V1:
 *   1. CRITICAL: Removed `or_state = OR_NORMAL` spurious reset at bottom of engine_step —
 *      it was wiping the overrange state machine every single sample.
 *   2. ppm lock now breaks immediately when II flips out of UP (+1),
 *      exactly matching Python IncrementalCompute (not gated on rec_pct==100).
 *   3. peak_M is now captured from M_prev (the M value from the sample just
 *      before the II transition), not from M_delta at the transition sample.
 *      This fixes recovery getting stuck at low concentrations where baseline
 *      is very close to peak.
 *   4. M_prev promoted from local static to engine-level state variable so
 *      do_calibrate() can properly reset it.
 *   5. run_mode() is now purely counter-based (no millis gating) — one ADC
 *      read = one engine step, every time through the loop.
 *   6. N_accum reset logic: when II transitions from UP→anything, N_accum
 *      is zeroed and lock is broken, matching Python exactly.
 *
 * Output columns (UART, space-separated, CR+LF):
 * [1] raw_emf_mV   — sensor_final_output in mV (e.g. 0012.345)
 * [2] ref_delta_mV — emf minus reference (e.g. +0000.123)
 * [3] ppm          — H2 concentration (e.g.   0 to 999999)
 * [4] flag         — AIR / UP / DOWN / REC / OVERRANGE / WAIT / STABLE
 * [5] recovery_pct — 0 to 100 (integer %)
 *
 * Serial command interface (9600 baud, framed *..#):
 * *RF<7-digit mV>#          — set reference (existing)
 * *T<4-digit limit><2-digit offset>#  — set filter limit+offset (existing)
 * *CAL#                     — trigger calibrate (master reset)
 * *SET JMP <float>#         — leaky snap threshold mV
 * *SET ALP <float>#         — leaky blend alpha
 * *SET UPG <float>#         — up gate count
 * *SET ING <float>#         — up intensity gate
 * *SET DNG <float>#         — down gate count
 * *SET DNI <float>#         — down intensity
 * *SET REC <float>#         — recovery threshold
 * *SET DRF <float>#         — baseline drift cap mV
 * *SET NTH <float>#         — N accumulation threshold fraction
 * *SET OCP <int>#           — ROC cap (o_cap)
 * *SET RZP <float>#         — recovery zero percent
 * *SET WRM <int>#           — warmup samples
 * *SET ORT <float>#         — overrange entry mV
 * *SET ORX <float>#         — overrange exit mV
 * *SET ORS <float>#         — overrange stable SD threshold
 * *SET CAL <idx> <mV> <ppm>#— edit calibration table (e.g. *SET CAL 3 4.2 100#)
 * *GET PARAMS#              — print all current params
 */

